    <h2>The Challenge</h2>
    <p>MOL Group, a leading integrated oil and gas company headquartered in Budapest, operates refineries across Central and Eastern Europe. With aging refinery infrastructure and increasingly stringent European regulatory requirements, MOL recognized the need to modernize its approach to asset integrity management. The existing integrity practices, while meeting minimum regulatory requirements, lacked the data-driven risk assessment capabilities needed to optimize inspection spending and demonstrate proactive safety management.</p>
    <p>MOL sought a solution that could accommodate multiple regulatory frameworks across different operating countries while providing a unified view of integrity risk across the enterprise.</p>

    <h2>The Partnership Approach</h2>
    <p>MOL selected a partnership between TUV Rheinland, a globally recognized inspection and certification body, and Metegrity to deliver a comprehensive AIM solution. TUV Rheinland provided deep expertise in European inspection standards, damage mechanism assessment, and RBI methodology. Metegrity contributed <strong>Visions Enterprise</strong> as the technology platform, along with implementation expertise from hundreds of global deployments.</p>
    <p>This combined approach ensured that the solution was technically rigorous, regulatory compliant, and practically implementable. TUV Rheinland engineers conducted damage mechanism reviews and RBI assessments while Metegrity consultants configured the platform and managed data migration from legacy systems.</p>

    <h2>The Results</h2>
    <p>The partnership delivered measurable outcomes for MOL Group:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Comprehensive RBI program</strong> covering over 15,000 equipment items across multiple refinery sites, fully aligned with API 580/581 and European Pressure Equipment Directive requirements.</li>
      <li><strong>Reduced inspection costs by 28%</strong> in the first inspection cycle following RBI implementation, through optimized scope and extended intervals for low-risk equipment.</li>
      <li><strong>Standardized integrity practices</strong> across all operating countries, enabling consistent risk assessment and reporting regardless of local regulatory variations.</li>
      <li><strong>Enhanced turnaround efficiency</strong>, with RBI-informed scope development reducing the integrity inspection component of turnaround duration by an average of three days.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Strategic Value</h2>
    <p>Beyond the immediate operational benefits, the MOL implementation demonstrated the value of partnering with complementary specialists rather than relying on a single vendor for both consulting and technology. The TUV Rheinland-Metegrity partnership provided MOL with independent technical expertise alongside proven technology, ensuring that the integrity program was built on sound engineering judgment supported by capable tools.</p>
    <p>MOL Group now uses the Visions Enterprise platform as a strategic decision-making tool, informing capital investment prioritization, turnaround planning, and long-term asset lifecycle management across its European operations.</p>
